  <li>NB: It is important to point out that the <code class="highlighter-rouge">reshape2</code> package which includes <code class="highlighter-rouge">melt</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">cast</code> has been superseded by the <a href="http://tidyr.tidyverse.org/">tidyr</a> package which includes <code class="highlighter-rouge">gather</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">spread</code>!</li>
  <li>But the original paper is still worth reading: <a href="https://www.jstatsoft.org/index.php/jss/article/view/v059i10/v59i10.pdf">Wickham, Hadley. 2014. ‚ÄúTidy Data.‚Äù Journal of Statistical Software Volume 59 (Issue 10)</a>  at some point (I bet it is summarized/explained even better in one of the books that Wickham wrote that I already bought like the <a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2017/01/24/p1-reading-hadley-wickhams-r-data-science-book/">R for Data Science</a> book:-) !)</li>
